# let create new columns from start_time

UNIVARIATE EXPLORATION¶

QUESTION 1 : How many Customers and Subscribers are the members of the bike riding system.¶

In [17]:
#creating function for the labels of visuals called plot_label

def plot_label(title,xlabel,ylabel):
    ''''
    This is function for labelling
    '''
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    plt.ylabel(ylabel)
    plt.show()
    
    
    # Show number of user using countplot

plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))     
base_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
ax = sb.countplot(data=my_data, x ='user_type', color=base_color)
plot_label('Number of each user type', 'user_type','Number')

The bar plot shows that Subscriber clients are more than Customer clients, the Customer clients are less than 20,000. while Subscriber clients is almost 160,000.¶

QUESTION 2 : What are the percentage of each rider.¶

In [18]:
# plot a pie chart
user_category = my_data['user_type'].value_counts()
plt.pie(user_category, explode =  (0, 0.2), labels = user_category.index, shadow = True, startangle = 45,
        counterclock = False, autopct='%1.2f%%');
plt.axis('square')
plt.show()

As shown from above, the percentage of Subscriber is 90.6% whole that of Customer is 9.4%.¶

Bivariate Exploration¶

QUESTION 6: Who among the the gender spend most time on riding bike?¶

In [22]:
plt.figure(figsize = [10, 5])
sb.boxplot(x='member_gender', y='duration_minutes', data = my_data, palette ='Set1', order=['Male', 'Female'])
plt.ylim(-10, 50)
plot_label('Trip Duration across Gender Types','Gender Type','Trip Duration (min)')

The average time spent by Female is more greater than Male, The boxplot does show that female gender has a higher trip duration than male.¶

Question 7: Which of the gender shared the ride with other when riding.¶

In [23]:

The viz showed that Male gender share more bike than their Female counterpart, the count bike share Male almost triple the Female one.¶

Question 8: What is average duration in minute for each gender during riding¶

In [24]:
#query the data for duration only below 1 hour to focus the data
my_data_dur = my_data.query("duration_minutes < 60")

# plot relationship between gender and duration
base_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
sb.violinplot(data=my_data_dur, x='member_gender', y='duration_minutes', color=base_color, inner='quartile')
plot_label('Duration Against User Gender','Gender','Duration (min)');

The plot looks similar for these two gender categories, with the median all similar around 10 minutes,but their third quarter is slightly difference.¶

Question 9: Which of the user type has higher duration during riding.¶

In [25]:

plot_label('Duration Against User Type','User Type','Duration (min)');

Customer clients ride duration is higher than that of Subcriber clients, while Subcriber clients are below ten minutes the Customer clients mark at fifteen minutes. This depicts that Customer clients rides bikes more than Subcriber clients.¶
